olive oil
2 clove garlic
1 cucumber
1 radish
1 packet beef mince
½ packet fine breadcrumbs
1 egg
1 packet Onion Chutney
1 bag Mixed Salad Leaves
1 drizzle balsamic vinegar
1 packet creamy pesto dressing
1 sachet Tuscan Herb Seasoning
1 carrot

• Finely chop garlic. Thinly slice cucumber and radish.
• Grate the carrot.

• In a medium bowl, combine beef mince, Tuscan herb seasoning, fine breadcrumbs (see ingredients), the egg, garlic and a pinch of salt and pepper.
• Using damp hands, roll heaped spoonfuls of beef mixture into small meatballs (4-5 per person). Transfer to a plate.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat.
• Cook meatballs, turning, until browned and cooked through, 8-10 minutes (cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded).
• Remove from heat, then add onion chutney and a splash of water. Toss meatballs to coat. Set aside.
• In a large bowl, combine mixed salad leaves, carrot, cucumber, radish, a drizzle of balsamic vinegar and olive oil. Season to taste.

• Divide garden salad between bowls.
• Top with Mediterranean beef meatballs and spoon over any remaining glaze.
• Drizzle with creamy pesto dressing to serve. Enjoy!